TASK 2 — Database Migration
Create db/migrations/001_exchange_accounts.sql.
This migration must:
Create the exchange_accounts table exactly as in MATP.SDD.md §5.1:
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS exchange_accounts (
    id          VARCHAR(100) PRIMARY KEY,
    exchange    VARCHAR(30) NOT NULL,
    mode        VARCHAR(10) NOT NULL CHECK (mode IN ('live', 'demo')),
    label       VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    credentials BYTEA NOT NULL,
    is_active   BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT TRUE,
    created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
);
Add account_id column to orders (nullable, no FK yet — safe migration):
ALTER TABLE orders ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS account_id VARCHAR(100);
Add account_id column to strategies (nullable for now):
ALTER TABLE strategies ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS account_id VARCHAR(100);
Add the updated_at trigger for exchange_accounts — copy the pattern from init.sql.
Add an index:
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS orders_account_id_idx ON orders (account_id);
Insert a seed row for the default Blofin demo account using a placeholder credential:
-- Seed: default account for migration. Credentials must be updated via Dashboard.
INSERT INTO exchange_accounts (id, exchange, mode, label, credentials)
VALUES (
    'acc_blofin_demo_default',
    'blofin',
    'demo',
    'Blofin Demo (default)',
    '\x00'::bytea   -- placeholder; real credentials set via Dashboard
) ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
Backfill: set account_id on all existing strategies that have platform = 'blofin':
UPDATE strategies
SET account_id = 'acc_blofin_demo_default'
WHERE account_id IS NULL AND platform IN ('blofin', 'auto');
Do NOT drop platform column — it must remain for backward compatibility. Do NOT alter init.sql — the migration is additive only.
After writing the file, verify it is valid SQL by checking for:
Balanced parentheses on every CREATE/ALTER statement
Semicolons on every statement
No references to columns that don't exist in init.sql
CHECKPOINT PROTOCOL
Before starting each task, update .gemini/CHECKPOINT.md:
status: in-progress
current_task: [task name]
After completing each task, update:
status: done
files_modified: [list]
If you are interrupted or run out of context, write to CHECKPOINT.md:
status: interrupted
interrupted_at: [describe exactly where you stopped]
next_step: [exactly what the next prompt should do to resume]
SESSION CLOSE PROTOCOL
When all tasks are done (or you are stopping for any reason):
Fill in .gemini/SESSION_LOG.md completely — every section.
Fill in .gemini/NEXT_SESSION.md — tell the next session exactly what it needs to know.
Fill in .gemini/REPORT_FOR_HUMAN.md — this is what the human will paste to Claude.
The human cannot see your work unless REPORT_FOR_HUMAN.md is complete.
FLASH LITE FALLBACK
If you are running on a reduced-capability model, Task 2 is safe to complete mechanically — it is pure SQL with no architectural decisions. Copy the exact SQL blocks from this prompt. Do not attempt to redesign the schema.
